This seems to be a regression introduced recently:
```
# git status
On branch yang-1.1
nothing to commit, working directory clean
```
```
# cat test.yang 
module test {
  yang-version 1.1;
  namespace "http://example.com/";
  prefix "t";

  container foo {
    action bar;
  }
}
```
```
# pyang --strict test.yang 
test.yang:2: error: bad value "1.1" (should be version)
test.yang:7: error: unexpected keyword "action"
```

Hi

I'm trying to crawl a list from a online video website. 

Here is the url
http://www.bilibili.com/newlist.html?page=1
http://www.bilibili.com/newlist.html?page=2
...

It's really weird that while crawling every page I get the same result as page 1.

Code:
````
#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Created on 2016-07-05 14:45:23
# Project: bilinew

from pyspider.libs.base_handler import *
import re

class Handler(BaseHandler):
    crawl_config = {
    }

    def __init__(self):
        self.base_url = 'http://www.bilibili.com/newlist.html?page='
        self.page_num = 1
        self.total_num = 30
    
    @every(minutes=24 * 60)
    def on_start(self):
        while self.page_num <= self.total_num:
            url = self.base_url + str(self.page_num)
            #print url
            self.crawl(url, callback=self.index_page)
            self.page_num += 1

    @config(age=10*24*60*60)
    def index_page(self, response):
        for each in response.doc('a[href^="http"]').items():
            if re.match("http://www.bilibili.com/video/av\d{7}", each.attr.href):
                self.crawl(each.attr.href, callback=self.detail_page)
        #self.crawl(response.doc('.nextPage').attr.href, callback=self.index_page)

    @config(priority=2)
    def detail_page(self, response):
        return {
            "url": response.url,
            "title": response.doc('title').text(),
        }
````

After digging deeper I find after I open one of the urls in my browser it can be crawled properly.

Any one can help me?

Thanks!

